Dear Harshitha,

This is going to be a raw, unpoetic prose, purely out of my heart, putting all words I have for you. I might not follow an order, a good language but that's how I really want to write to you.

We keep hearing people in stories telling someone that "You are the most beautiful thing ever happened to me." I always wondered how that feeling would be and probably only romantic relationships can give us that feeling.

And then, eventually I met you.

I was not expecting anything from you by the time we met, probably that is the reason why our relationship turned out to be this beautiful. We have already discussed 1000 times about how we naturally went with the flow when we met for the first time.

But, I want to add something to our first meet analogy. We think that we got along, because we were dealing with similar men/personal lives. But I feel, that the fact that we got along so easily is because, we share similar versions of ourselves, on how we see things around. So everything we spoke to each other, got along with "exactly".

Or probably, we are connected from previous life, (ðŸ˜›).

I feel, I can do anything and everything on the globe, good bad or whatever and come to you and rant out about it, with no feeling of judgement at all. And that's incredible.

From the day we met, you had to play the role of mom, dad, sibling, boyfriend ðŸ˜› everything in my life. Of course you don't have a choice. But, here I want to tell you something.

I never had a sister or even a distant sister in my life. I always had a feeling that I am a third person in anyone's life, especially in friendships and I was okay with it. This has been my personal feeling since childhood, while I have many close friends, I always have a feeling that I am never that important in their lives and always compared myself with other friends. This is a deepest insecurity I have and I somehow accepted it.

And then entered you, my beautiful lady!

You did the magic, you give me a feeling that, no matter where you are, I always have a special place in your heart which is irreplaceable.

That is the most beautiful feeling in the world, and you made me feel it for the first time.

I always have a feeling that, no matter how much ever love or affection I give to you, it is always less than how much you give me. And I can never give you competition in it.

With all my love,
